@node "INSTALL" "SN XFerTracker v1.2 - Installation Procedures"
@toc "MAIN"
┌───────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  SN XFerTracker v1.2 - Installation Procedures
└───────────────────────────────────────────────┘

 1  Run the included installation script either of the following
    two ways:

    a.  Type "Installer Install_AutoUL" from the Shell.

    b.  Click on the "Install_AutoUL" icon from Workbench.

 2  The installation script moves the required files to your specified
    location, including adding a CNet help file called "UL."

 3  At the bottom of "2; Available everywhere" items in bbsmenu, add the
    following lines:

      ULT |{#0PFiles:SN_XFerTracker U}
      DLT |{#0PFiles:SN_XFerTracker D}

    Note that the above { is actually a control-Q command and you should
    substitute PFiles for where ever you actually installed the files to.

 4  Add the above commands (ULT and DLT) to your user menus and let them
    know about it.  (If you choose to do so.)

 5  Add the following to your events:

      Command:    RunARexx
      Args:       PFiles:SN_XFerTracker M
      Port(s):    0 (or whatever port you run your maintenance on)
      Type:       Immediate--system idle or not
      Days:       SSMTWTF
      Time:       0 (or whenever you want)
      Valid:      1
      Interval:   0
      Iterate:    1

 6  Reload your bbstext/bbsmenu via CNet's Control Panel menu (option
    #3, "Text/menu reload  RAmiga-T" and you're all set!

 7  Nothing else must modify or delete CNet's upload/download logs.
    (Including YOU!)  If anything does, the reports are not going to
    be accurate, obviously.  A nightly report will be mailed to you
    detailing the day's uploads and downloads.

───SN/AHI (910) 326-3804 (28.8k)─────────────────────────────────────────
